He may not be the "best" creature in Magic, but flavour wise he is definitely my favourite. Still working on a re-animate deck to put him in.  

@Cloudye; Griselbrand can easily (well on a good draw) hit the table turn one....and then you're opponent hits him with a [Swords to Plowshares](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Swords to Plowshares). Sad Panda.  

@Smoke\_Stack: Still doesn't beat a Turn 1 Griselbrand! ;)  

@Lifegainwithbite: Legacy? Who said Legacy? That's my play in Casual, lol (well sometimes it's [Jin-Gitaxias, Core Augur](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jin-Gitaxias, Core Augur)). Generally Legacy players don't run Ritual; they keep the space for [Force of Will](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Force of Will) and [Daze](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Daze).
